# Workflow Session Rules

## Start Project
When user says "Start Project", "Begin Project", "Start Session", or "Cold Start":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/Start-Project.md` workflow
- Read mandatory docs in order (README.md, START-HERE.md, project-log.md, Checkpoint.md)
- Run lightweight pre-flight environment checks
- DO NOT auto-start development servers

## End Project
When user says "End Project", "End Session", "Close Session", or "Session Closeout":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/End-Project.md` workflow
- Summarize changes, update tracking logs, run Git audits, and prompt for commits
- Clean up active listeners/ports (port 3000)

## Update Docs
When user says "update docs":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/Update-Docs.md` workflow
- Scan, sync, and resolve any documentation inconsistencies
- Log recent fixes to ISSUES-RESOLVED.md

## Update Project
When user says "Update Project" or "Sync Project":
- Execute `.cursor/prompts/Update-Project.md` workflow
- Automatically detect git history/recent commits to sync project-log.md and Checkpoint.md
